Annotated Turing
----------------

I wrote this code because I wanted to try out the examples from the book
The Annotated Turing (http://www.theannotatedturing.com/) by Charles Petzold.

To use it (in Emacs/Slime), simply C-x C-f ch5.lisp, C-c C-k and do:

; Constructs the example from page 81
CL-USER> (p81)
NEXT

; Step through the program with next
CL-USER> (next)

TAPE: 0_  NEXT: C
       ^  STEP: 1
NIL
CL-USER> (next 3)
TAPE: 0_1__  NEXT: B
          ^  STEP: 4
NIL
CL-USER> (next 100)
TAPE: 0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1_0_1__  NEXT: B
                                                                                                              ^  STEP: 104
NIL

; Constructs the example from page 87
CL-USER> (p87)
NEXT
CL-USER> (next 1000)
TAPE: @@0_0_1_0_1_1_0_1_1_1_0_1_1_1_1_0_1_1_1_1_1_0_1_1_1_1_1_1_0_1_1_1_1_1_1_1_0_1_1_1_1_1_1_1_1_0_1_1_1_1_1_1_1_1_1  NEXT: .P
                                     ^                                                                                 STEP: 1000
NIL
CL-USER> 